## 🎯 WHAT THE SCRIPT DOES

### Phase 1: Gaming Scan 🎮
- Scans `C:\Program Files`, `C:\Program Files (x86)`, `C:\`
- Identifies: Steam, Epic Games, Ubisoft, Battle.net, Riot Games, Xbox Games
- Reports folders > 1GB

### Phase 2: Ghost Apps 👻
- Scans `%LOCALAPPDATA%`, `%APPDATA%`
- Identifies: Adobe, DaVinci Resolve, Visual Studio, Android Studio
- Reports folders > 500MB

### Phase 3: Forgotten Files 🗑️
- Scans Downloads, Desktop, Documents
- Identifies files > 1GB
- Extensions: .iso, .zip, .rar, .7z, .exe, .mp4, .mkv

### Phase 4: Suspicious Folders ❓
- Scans C:\ root
- Identifies: Backup, Copy, Old, Temp, Archive folders
- Reports folders > 100MB

---

## 📊 EXPECTED OUTPUT

The script will create:
- **Report file:** `Desktop\DeepClean_Report\scan_results_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.txt`
- **Automatic open:** Report opens in Notepad when complete

**Report sections:**
1. 🎮 Gaming Installations (with sizes)
2. 👻 Heavy Applications (with sizes)
3. 🗑️ Forgotten Files (with sizes)
4. ❓ Suspicious Folders (with sizes)
5. 📊 Final Summary (total recoverable space)

---

## ⚠️ SAFETY FEATURES

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The script is **READ-ONLY** - it will NOT delete anything!

- Only scans and reports
- No files are moved or deleted
- Waits for explicit "DELETE" or "MOVE" command
- All actions require manual approval

